  "doc_id": "38995",
  "text": "Patients who manifest findings of IRIS while receiving effective antiretroviral therapy at the time of diagnosis should continue it and begin treatment for histoplasmosis. A two-week delay is recommended in patients who are not receiving antiretroviral treatment. [CITATION_1] The role of corticosteroids is unclear 110 but may be appropriate in patients with more severe manifestations [CITATION_2] if they are receiving amphotericin B or itraconazole, which should prevent progression of histoplasmosis.",
